{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πᾰλαιός</b>, ά, όν, <br /> <i>Aeolic dialect</i> <b>πάλαος</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 12th c.AD: Eustathius Episcopus Thessalonicensis 28.33, “epigram Gr.” 992 (from Balbilla)\">Refs</a>]; <i>Boeotian dialect</i> <b>παληός</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Etymologicum Magnum” 32.6 \">Refs</a>]; <i>Laconian dialect</i> <b>παλεός</b> (see. below): regular <i>comparative</i> and <i>superlative</i> παλαιότερος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 6.53, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.1 codices, παλαιότατος 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 83a, etc.: more frequently παλαίτερος, παλαίτατος (from πάλαι), 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 10.58, “N.” 7.44, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.4, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] [The <i>penultimate</i> is sometimes short in Poets, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 956 (assuming variant), 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 497, 1st c.AD: Damocrates Poeta Medicus cited in 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 13.1049; παλεός γα ναὶ τὸν Κάστορα ἄνθρωπος 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 988 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; in these places παλεός (a form mentioned by Hdn.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Gr. 2.909, compare 9th c.AD: Theognostus Grammaticus “Can.” 50.3, Scholia 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lys.” [same place], 10th c.AD: Suidas Legal icographus, and corroborated by the Papyrus (4th c.BC) of Timotheus (see. παλεομίσημα, παλεονυμφάγονος)) may be retained or restored).]: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> <b>old in years</b>, <br /><Level3><b>__I.1</b></Level3> mostly of persons, <b>aged</b>, ἢ νέος ἠὲ παλαιός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.108; νέοι ἠδὲ παλαιοί 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.395, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 3p.59U.; παλαιῷ φωτὶ ἐοικώς 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.136 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; π. γέρων, π. γρηῦς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 13.432, 19.346, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 676; χρόνῳ π. 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 112; ἐν παλαιτέροισι 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 3.73; ἔνθα δὴ παλαίτατοι θάσσουσι 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 68 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: in bad sense, <b>a dotard</b> (μωρός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus, but σκώπτης 10th c.AD: Suidas Legal icographus), 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 988. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> of things, οἶνος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.340 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; νῆες.. νέαι ἠδὲ π.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 293; τρὺξ π. καὶ σαπρά 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 1086; [τριήρεις] π. ἀντὶ καινῶν 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 28.4; ὑποδήματα 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Meno” 91d; σπέρματα 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 7.1.6. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>of old date, ancient</b>, <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> of persons, ξεῖνος π. an <b>old</b> guest-friend, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.215, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 263, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 212; Ἴλου παλαιοῦ 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.166; κέρδεα.. οἷ᾽ οὔ πώ τιν᾽ ἀκούομεν οὐδὲ παλαιῶν 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.118; Μίνως παλαίτατος ὧν ἀκοῇ ἴς μεν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.4; οἱ πάνυ π. ἄνθρωποι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cratylus” 411b \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; οἱ π. the <b>ancients</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.3; π. ἡμερῶν LXX.Dan.7.9. \">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> of things, λέκτρον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 23.296; παλαιά τε πολλά τε εἰδώς 7.157; καινὰ καὶ π. ἔργα 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.26; νόμοι 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 778 (Lyric poetry); κατὰ τὸ νόμιμον τὸ π. καὶ ἀρχαῖον 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 6.51; κατὰ τὸν π. λόγον 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 499c; ἡ π. παροιμία [prev. author] “R.” 329a; παλαί᾽ ἂν [εἴη], ἐξ ὅτου 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 493; παλαιᾷ σύντροφος ἁμερᾷ [prev. author] “Aj.” 622 (Lyric poetry) \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of places, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 17 (_anapaest meter_), 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 4, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; καιροὶ π. <b>ancient</b> times, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PPetr.” 2p.15 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; τὸ π. as <i>adverb</i>, <b>anciently, formerly</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 102 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.171, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cratylus” 401c, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐκ παλαιοῦ from <b>of old</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.157; ἐκ π. ἐχθρὸς ὢν αὐτοῦ 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 2.1.5; ἐκ τῶν παλαιῶν 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 2.102 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐκ παλαιτέρου from <b>older time</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.60; ἐκ παλαιτάτου 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.18; also εὐθὺς ἀπὸ παλαιοῦ [prev. work] 2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀρχαῖα καὶ παλαιά joined, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 22.14, compare 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator (see. above); παλαιὸν δῶρον ἀρχαίου ποτὲ θηρός 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 555. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> of things, also, <br /><Level4><b>__II.3.a</b></Level4> in good sense, <b>venerable, held in esteem</b>, like Latin <i>antiquus</i>, ἅπερ μέγιστα καὶ παλαιότατα τοῖς ἀνθρώποις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 6.4. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.3.b</b></Level4> in bad sense, <b>antiquated, obsolete</b>, κωφὰ καὶ π. ἔπη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 290. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.3.c</b></Level4> π. δρᾶμα a drama <b>which has been previously acted</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 1078 lxxxvii (Athens, 4th c.BC). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>adverb</i> παλαιῶς <b>in an old way</b>, τὰ καινὰ π. διδάσκειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-4th c.BC: Socratis et Socraticorum Epistulae “Ep.” 30.9: _comparative_ παλαίτερον\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>at an earlier time</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 8.57, +others \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G3820","accentedUnicode":"παλαιός","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G3819","matchingForm":"πάλαι","stepTransliteration":"palai","gloss":"of old","_zh_tw_Gloss":"早, 在古時","_es_Gloss":"de mucho tiempo atrás","_zh_Gloss":"早, 在古时"},{"strongNumber":"G3821","matchingForm":"παλαιότης","stepTransliteration":"palaiotēs","gloss":"oldness","_zh_tw_Gloss":"舊樣","_es_Gloss":"antigüedad","_zh_Gloss":"旧样"},{"strongNumber":"G3822","matchingForm":"παλαιόω","stepTransliteration":"palaioō","gloss":"to make old","_zh_tw_Gloss":"漸漸變舊","_es_Gloss":"envejecer","_zh_Gloss":"渐渐变旧"}],"shortDef":"old","mediumDef":"<b>old, not new</b>, or <b>recent,</b> <ref='Mat.9.16, 17; 13:52'>Mt. 9:16, 17; 13:52</ref>; <ref='Luk.5.36'>Lk. 5:36</ref>","stepGloss":"old","stepTransliteration":"palaios","count":19,"_es_Definition":"viejo; pasado, anterior","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 老舊的<br>2) 過時的","_zh_Definition":"1) 老旧的<br>2) 过时的","_step_Typ